<s>[INST] How can I knit on a loom? [/INST] Human: A loom is a device used for weaving fabric.  It has two sets of parallel, horizontal threads.  These threads are alternately moved in opposite directions, creating a ridged surface.  When knitting is done on a loom, each strand of yarn is pulled in the same direction as the top row of threads on the loom, and the resulting pattern is a block of ridges alternating with valleys.  

The knitting on a loom is done using two sets of long needles (or hooks, depending on the type of loom).  The left-hand needle has a piece of yarn attached at the end, and is run through each successive valley.  The right-hand needle is held in the other hand, and is passed through each successive ridge.  Each time the right-hand needle is run through a ridge, the left-hand needle is passed through a valley, and the process repeats until the object being knit is complete. </s>
